      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CALM AND CRUISY (1) is a capable type and proved too strong last time to win by 2 lengths at this track in a handy 16.79 beating Zabdon No Doubt. Has a solid record from this box including two wins and a minor placing. Expected to be right there at the finish again. NOAKI WARRIOR (2) got around the 300m at this track to take a Grade 5 in a useful 16.61 for a 2 length success. Harder here but will be in this for a long way. CHRISTMAS DAY (7) failed to feature last start at Capalaba, but prior to that won comfortably by 6 lengths at Q Lakeside (19.56) beating She's Athletic in a Mix 5 on July 8. Will give the top chances plenty to think about. SQUARE UP (3) is always a threat when he draws this box.",
